meaning_str.bing:
n. 目标；物体；目的；东西
v. 反对；不同意；不赞成；提出…作为反对的理由
网络. 对象；物件；宾语

反对；不同意；不赞成；提出…作为反对的理由

反对；不赞成；不同意；提出异议；抗议；提出反对意见
物体；东西；目标；目的；（极欲得到、研究、注意等的）对象；[计算机]对象；宾语；客体；宗旨

1.en: Now that you know the name of the file, you can read this file into its own simpleXML object.
1.cn: 现在您知道了文件名，可以将此文件读入到它自己的simpleXML对象中。

2.en: After a year of studying Vesta, Dawn is scheduled to leave orbit and, in 2015, approach the only asteroid-belt object that is larger: Ceres.
2.cn: 一年后，黎明号探测器将离开灶神星的轨道，计划在2015年到达谷神星，它是小行星带中唯一一颗比灶神星大的小行星。

3.en: Even a man of very bad temper is not angry at it because there is no object being against to.
3.cn: 这时，不论您的脾气有多坏，您也不会生气，因为没有生气的对象嘛！

0.en: I object. You're completely ignoring the law.
0.cn: 我反对，你这是在无视法律。

1.en: You should object. Objection, Your Honor. Relevance? Good guess. No.
1.cn: 你应该说反对。反对，法官阁下，无相关性？猜得很用心，但错了。

2.en: Increased acceleration toward the object. Estimated contact within two minutes.
2.cn: 朝目标移动的加速度已增加。预计两分钟后到达目标。

3.en: Every planet orbiting a luminous object is casting a shadow out into space.
3.cn: 绕着恒星运行的每一个行星，都会向太空投射阴影。

4.en: A hidden object in a game that gives special powers to whoever discovers it.
4.cn: 彩蛋隐藏在游戏中将赐予发现它的玩家特殊的奖励。

5.en: How many times? I again object to this line of questioning as a delaying tactic.
5.cn: 试了几次? 我再次反对用这类问题作为推迟的策略。

6.en: The philosopher Henri Bergson says it's funny when a human being behaves like an object.
6.cn: 但哲学家亨利柏格林说当人类表现得和物体一样时，就会很好笑。

7.en: Excuse me. I object. You propose a guessing game yet you don't give me enough time to guess.
7.cn: 抱歉，我反对，你提出的是一个猜谜游戏，可是你一点猜的时间都不给我。

8.en: I don't object to the concept of a deity, but I'm baffled by the notion of one that takes attendance.
8.cn: 我并不反对神的概念，但实在不理解上教堂还得点名。

9.en: And I don't want to be joined to another object by an inclined plane wrapped helically around an axis.
9.cn: 我不想变成一个斜面绕轴螺旋状转上几圈之后的样子。

10.en: Like what? I don't know. Is there another job that I could cross-examine people and yell "I object" a lot?
10.cn: 比如什么？不知道有没有别的什么工作，既能盘问别人又能经常大喊"我反对"。

11.en: That in the face of true love, you don't just give up, even if the object of your affection is begging you to.
11.cn: 在真爱面前，你永远不要放弃，即使是你爱的人求你放过她。

12.en: These past months have been a torment. I came to Rosings with the single object of seeing you. I had to see you.
12.cn: 这几个月对于我来说是一种折磨，我来罗新斯只是为了见你。

13.en: Thanks, but if you want to talk impressive, this guy right here discovered a planetary object outside the Kuiper belt.
13.cn: 谢谢，但如果要说厉害，这家伙可是在凯伯带以外发现了一个行星体。

14.en: Colonel Forster is a sensible man. He will keep her out of any real mischief. And she's far too poor to be an object of prey to anyone.
14.cn: 费斯托上校是个有见识的人，他不会让她闯出什么祸事来的。她太穷，谁也不会看中她。

15.en: I know Remy has just briefed you all, so, aside from the Secretary of Homeland Security, who is no longer with us, does anyone else object to this plan?
15.cn: 我知道雷米已经向各位介绍过情况了，那么，除了国土安全部部长已经离职之外，还有谁持反对意见吗？（除了已经离职的国土安全部部长之外）

16.en: With the understanding that nothing changes whatsoever, physical or otherwise, I would not object to us no longer characterizing you as "not my girlfriend."
16.cn: 基于无论如何都维持原状的共识，包括身体或其他方面，我将不会不同意也不再把你定位为“不是我女朋友”。

17.en: So Leonard, how goes the mimesis? Mimesis? You know. Mimesis. An action in which the mimic takes on the properties of a specific object or organism. Mimesis.
17.cn: 莱纳德，鹦鹉学舌得怎么样？鹦鹉学舌？你知道的，鹦鹉学舌，就是鹦鹉学着某个特定的目标或人物模仿他们的行为。鹦鹉学舌。

18.en: My object in coming to Longbourn was to choose such a one from among Mr Bennet's daughters, for I am to inherit the estate and such an alliance will surely suit everyone.
18.cn: 我来浪博恩的目的就是从班纳特先生的女儿中挑选一个做太太，因为我将要继承令尊的财产，而像这样的结合一定会让每个人满意。

19.en: Meet chimp nine. Here she is tasking at what is called the Lucas Tower, the object of which is to move the tower from peg to peg, without placing a larger block on top of a smaller block.
19.cn: 来见见九号猩猩。视频中她正在玩汉诺塔游戏的目标是通过在三根柱子间调整每层塔的位置使塔层从大到小排列游戏中大片不能压在小片上面。
